        {
            "id": "80d339aba2f7422dac360",
            "questionText": "Consider a cup of hot tea at a temperature of $!$353.15\\,K$!$ with a dynamic viscosity of $!$0.0005\\,Pa\\cdot s$!$. A sugar molecule dissolved in the tea can be approximated as a sphere with a radius of $!$5\\times10^{-10}\\,m$!$. Using the Einstein relation for diffusion $!$D=\\frac{k_B T}{6\\pi\\eta r}$!$ where the Boltzmann constant $!$k_B=1.38\\times10^{-23}\\,J/K$!$, calculate the diffusion coefficient $!$D$!$ of the sugar molecule in the tea. Provide your answer in $!$m^2/s$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "832384f99ace4d0a89485",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct form of the Einstein relation for diffusion. Please select the correct formula from the options below.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$D=\\frac{k_B T}{6\\pi\\eta r}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$D=\\frac{k_B T}{3\\pi\\eta r}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$D=\\frac{k_B T}{4\\pi\\eta r}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "32d99d5425ac4346ba7cd",
                    "stepText": "Great, now let's compute the numerator of the Einstein relation, which is the product $!$k_B \\times T$!$. Use the values $!$k_B = 1.38\\times10^{-23}\\,J/K$!$ and $!$T = 353.15\\,K$!$. What is the result of this multiplication?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4.88e-21"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "J",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "759eb2ce9b7941aa886cb",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the denominator of the relation given by $!$6\\pi\\eta r$!$. Here, $!$\\eta = 0.0005\\,Pa\\cdot s$!$ and $!$r = 5\\times10^{-10}\\,m$!$. What value do you obtain for the denominator?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4.7125e-12"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Pa\u00b7s\u00b7m",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "eb11164e8d294ccd91756",
                    "stepText": "Finally, determine the diffusion coefficient $!$D$!$ by dividing the numerator by the denominator. What is the diffusion coefficient in $!$m^2/s$!$?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1.036e-9"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m^2/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
